  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether the use of a mobile sensing platform in a
      primary care setting has an effect on provider workflows, patient outcomes, patient
      engagement, patient self-help behavior, health research, and total cost of care.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
